songs.title: Searching for You
songs.lyrics:
At least fifty people sitting by the tables all around the pub
Yet the one you want is nowhere to be found
You're sitting all by yourself all alone
Feeling like you just want to go home (where is home)

Everyone's talking in tones they understand
You try your best to make sense of what you heard
But your mayweather friends talk to each other like childhood buddies
Which makes you wonder if you're the only one who's not their best friend
(you're not their best friend)

The lights flicker softly shadows dancing on the walls
Glasses clink laughter echoes down the hall
You sip your drink pretending it's all okay
Hoping somehow this night won't slip away

Alone in the pub but I'm searching for you
All these faces none of them feel true
Alone in the pub you want nothing but to go home (where is home)
Find a place where I belong
Under the city sun
Under the city sun
Under the city sun
Aah

You catch a glimpse of someone across the room
A fleeting smile but then they're gone too soon (ooh)
The music hums your heartbeat keeps in time
With all the strangers' voices weaving through your mind (do you know)

And though you feel invisible in the crowd tonight
You dream of stepping out into the city lights
Finding someone who'll see you not just the space you're in
A quiet kind of magic where a lonely night could begin
(let it end)

songs.title: restless hands
songs.lyrics:
Silhouettes of strangers swaying to a mighty beat
Drowning in a gun full of sweet rivers of smiles
I could've had anything but your hungry eyes locked on me
Empty as the space that swallows this crowded party

I remember your restless hands all over me
I was your lucky strike and you were my night
Arms pulling me in keeping us up till dawn
Legs tangled tight holding on with all our might

Strobes of green and red yet you were gone
Nowhere in sight
Out of my mind for the rest of the night
Like this song I hum to you ours was loud enough to wake the block
One more second and the neighbors would've called it in

You were my hope and I was your fuck
That night I wish had stayed just a dream
I'd turn back time to catch your gaze again
On whatever piece of cake or cherry on top
You thought I was for you

I remember your restless hands all over me
I was your lucky strike and you were my night
Arms pulling me in keeping us up till dawn
Legs tangled tight holding on with all our might

Your white cotton vest
I didn't know I'd miss
Now your couch once the place where magic happened
Is just a pre party stop
The late night exchange of filthy words not meant to wound
You were there when the marks on my neck
Mirrored yours

I remember your restless hands all over me
I was your lucky strike and you were my night
Arms pulling me in keeping us up till dawn
Legs tangled tight holding on with all our might
